==English==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|lerned}}, {{m|enm|lernd}}, {{m|enm|lernyd}}, equivalent to {{affix|en|learn|-ed}}, which replaced the earlier {{m|enm|lered||taught}}, from {{der|en|ang|lǣred|(ġe)lǣred}}, past participle of {{m|ang|lǣran||to teach}}.<ref>{{R:OED Online|code=106719|part of speech=adj}}</ref> ''Learn'' formerly had the meaning “to teach”, which is now found only in nonstandard speech, as well as its standard meaning of “to learn”.

